            "questionText": "A high-speed train is traveling at a constant speed of $!$180 \\text{ km/h}$!$ on a straight, horizontal track. The vertical component of the Earth's magnetic field in that region is $!$50 \\text{ }\\mu\\text{T}$!$. The distance between the rails is $!$1.5 \\text{ m}$!$. Assuming the rails are electrically isolated except for a section $!$5 \\text{ km}$!$ down the track where they are connected by a resistive load of $!$0.1 \\Omega$!$, determine the magnitude of the current flowing through this resistive load due to the motional EMF induced in the train's axles.",
