            "id": "24dc3f7af4eb4786941b8",
            "questionText": "A transformer in a residential neighborhood steps down the voltage from the utility pole to household levels. The primary coil is connected to an AC voltage source of $!$2400 \\text{ V}$!$, and has $!$1200$!$ turns. The secondary coil, which supplies power to a house, has $!$60$!$ turns and is connected to a load that draws a current of $!$20 \\text{ A}$!$. If the transformer is $!$95\\%$!$ efficient, calculate the magnetic flux through each turn of the secondary coil, assuming the frequency of the AC voltage is $!$60 \\text{ Hz}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
